definition: United Kingdom/British/England/English/abbr. for 英國|英国[Ying1 guo2]
surname Ji/abbr. for Jilin Province 吉林省[Ji2 lin2 Sheng3]
ocean/sea/CL:個|个[ge4],片[pian4]/great number of people or things/(dialect) numerous

sentences.english: We took a hovercraft across the English Channel.
sentences.chinese: 我們乘氣墊船橫渡英吉利海峽。

sentences.english: Eg: She failed in her attempt to swim the tunnel.
sentences.chinese: 她橫度英吉利海峽的嘗試失敗了。

sentences.english: They bored a tunnel under the English Channel.
sentences.chinese: 他們在英吉利海峽下面開鑿了隧道。

sentences.english: The girl kept in training all the year round in the hope of swimming the English Channel in the summer.
sentences.chinese: 那女子常年堅持訓練，希望能在夏季橫渡英吉利海峽。

sentences.english: Who first swam the English Channel?
sentences.chinese: 第一個遊過英吉利海峽？

sentences.english: Debbi Hart is going to swim across the English Channel tomorrow.
sentences.chinese: 黛比哈特明天打算游泳橫渡英吉利海峽。

sentences.english: Erna Hart is going to swim across the English Channel tomorrow.
sentences.chinese: 哈特准備明天游泳橫渡英吉利海峽。

sentences.english: What did Jane do when she and her family were travelling across the Channel?
sentences.chinese: 當簡和她的家人在橫渡英吉利海峽時簡做了什麼？

sentences.english: The English Channel has often been swum.
sentences.chinese: 時常有人遊過英吉利海峽。

sentences.english: Jersey is anisland in the English Channel between Englandand France.
sentences.chinese: 澤西島位於英吉利海峽，處在英法之間。

sentences.english: I've been to the English Channel.
I have never sailed across the English Channel.
sentences.chinese: 我未曾橫渡過英吉利海峽。

sentences.english: The first was the blockading of the English Channel with mine barrages.
sentences.chinese: 首先利用佈設水雷封鎖英吉利海峽。

sentences.english: She had the distinction of being the first woman to swim the Channel.
sentences.chinese: 她作爲第一個遊過英吉利海峽的婦女而聞名於世。

sentences.english: England is separated from France by the Channel.
sentences.chinese: 英法兩國由英吉利海峽隔開。

sentences.english: Steam boats carried thousands of visitors across the channel from Europe.
sentences.chinese: 蒸汽輪船把成千上萬的人從歐洲送過英吉利海峽。
